Durban Two days after a SANDF soldier shot dead his girlfriend and her female friend, as well as wounding two other people in Ntuzuma, a police manhunt has yet to yield any results.Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said that as of Thursday morning, the soldier from 8 South African Infantry Battalion in Upington had not been apprehended despite a manhunt for him.The rifleman was, according to SANDF spokesperson Brigadier General Mafi Mgobozi, supposed to go on guard duty in Upington on Monday. He drew his weapon an R4 assault rifle then disappeared from his base in Upington.The following day he is alleged to have fatally shot his girlfriend and a friend, and wounded a bystander in Ntuzuma, on Durban s outskirts. A police officer who tried to intervene was also wounded and is recovering in hospital.The soldier was reportedly angered by the fact that his girlfriend had allegedly cheated on him. African News Agency</p> DURBAN, February 2 (ANA) Two days after a South African National Defence Force (SANDF) soldier shot dead his girlfriend and her female friend, as well as wounding two other people in Ntuzuma, a police manhunt for the man has yet to yield any results.</p> Police spokeswoman, Captain Nqobile Gwala, said that as of Thursday morning, the soldier from 8 South African Infantry Battalion in Upington had not been apprehended despite a manhunt for him.</p> The rifleman was, according to SANDF spokesman, Brigadier General Mafi Mgobozi, supposed to go on guard duty in Upington on Monday. He drew his weapon an R4 assault rifle and then disappeared from his base in Upington.</p> The following day he is alleged to have fatally shot his girlfriend and a friend, and wounded a bystander in Ntuzuma, on Durban s outskirts. A police officer who tried to intervene was also wounded and is recovering in hospital.</p> African News Agency (ANA)</p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> </p> DURBAN, February 2 (ANA) Two days after a Sou